Brace yourselves for some snow in parts of the country. Forecasters tell us temperatures are going to drop drastically this week. Kumsa Masizana from the Weather Service explains what we can expect. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Wet and cold weather is expected around South Africa this week. Snow is likely to fall in parts of the Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal and the Free State. The SA Weather Service is warning of thunderstorms and flooding in some areas.